Package grafiosch.gtnet

Class ExchangeKindTypeRegistry

java.lang.Object
grafiosch.gtnet.ExchangeKindTypeRegistry
@Component public class ExchangeKindTypeRegistry extends Object
Registry for exchange kind types that supports application-specific implementations. This registry provides a unified lookup mechanism for exchange kinds, allowing application modules to register their own IExchangeKindType implementations and retrieve them by their byte value.

Usage

Application-specific exchange kinds should be registered at startup via registerExchangeKind(IExchangeKindType). Use getByValue(byte) to retrieve exchange kinds by their byte value.

Example

 // At startup (e.g., in GTStartUp)
 for (GTNetExchangeKindType kind : GTNetExchangeKindType.values()) {
     exchangeKindTypeRegistry.registerExchangeKind(kind);
 }

 // Later in code
 IExchangeKindType kind = exchangeKindTypeRegistry.getByValue((byte) 0);

    • getSyncableKinds

      public Set<IExchangeKindType> getSyncableKinds()
      Returns all exchange kinds that participate in bulk synchronization. These are kinds where IExchangeKindType.isSyncable() returns true. Syncable kinds participate in data request/accept/revoke flows. Non-syncable kinds (like SECURITY_METADATA) use on-demand lookup patterns.
      Returns:
      set of syncable exchange kinds
